
1) What is a Java package?

    Packages are groups of related classes.

2) What is the CLASSPATH variable all about?

    Are the directory path or paths for packages and this is done by setting the CLASSPATH
    environmental variable.

3) What does the package structure mirror?

4 How do packages affect access to Java classes?

    The visibility of an element is determined by its accesses specification and the package in which it resides.
    The visibility of an element is determined by its visibility within a class and its visibility within a package.

5) What is an interface?

    A set of methods that will be implemented by a class. They have no body (no implementation).

6) What makes interfaces unique?

    It gives you a way to specify what a class will do, but not how it wil do it.

7) What keyword is used to specify that a class is going to use a separate interface?

    Interface

8) What makes interfaces so useful?

    You can separate a class' interface from its implementation

9) What was added in JDK 8 that makes interfaces even more useful?

    That it is possible to add a default implementation to an interface method.
    It is possible for interface to specify some behavior.

10) How many interfaces can a single class implement?

    More than one.